(Open a fruit shop for her)

68
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,080
Gao, why are you in the dorm?

69
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:46,980
No class today?

70
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,160
Doesn't seem like it.

71
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,060
Why not train?

72
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,520
I'll go later.

73
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:56,060
(How to cheer a girl: Do something)

74
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,840
Gao.

75
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,560
Is something wrong?

76
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,970
What could be wrong?

77
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,640
Weilan's mad at you?

78
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,440
Sort of.

79
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:19,920
I...

80
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,460
I said the wrong thing that day.

81
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,220
Why did you tell them that?

82
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,400
Are we supposed to bear the blame forever?

83
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,220
I just wanted to prove our strength.

84
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,180
I know you want to,

85
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,220
but such matches

86
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:36,260
drain you greatly.

87
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,500
Do you know that?

88
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:40,780
Compared to clearing our name,

89
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,420
this little exhaustion is nothing.

90
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,780
Really? You said that to her?

91
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,580
I was just being honest.

92
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:54,520
Girls need to be coaxed,

93
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,800
not lectured.

94
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,260
Anyone would be mad that way.

95
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,440
Well.

96
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,940
Should I lie to her?

97
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,140
You can't lie, but you

98
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,320
need to understand

99
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,380
talking to girls requires skill.

100
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,080
When you compliment her,

101
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,660
make it subtle.

102
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:11,940
Even if she's wrong,

103
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,300
encourage her positively.

104
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:16,300
Chen Weilan just wants to play.

105
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,360
You don't support it.

106
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:18,380
But how can you stop her?

107
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,020
Right, right, right.

108
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,380
I was too harsh.

109
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,800
After all, she's risking

110
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,800
getting injured for this.

111
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,640
Exactly.

112
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,240
So what should I do?

113
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,480
Apologize.

114
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,040
But

115
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,340
if you don't want to apologize,

116
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,740
there's another way.

117
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:41,920
What way?

118
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,700
Just find another path.

119
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,220
Like Yang Jingxuan.

120
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,580
Go away.

121
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:48,000
You're full of bad ideas.

122
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,840
Then you should

123
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:49,760
switch to Tu.

124
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:52,020
Why would I switch to Tu Lingling?

125
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,100
What's wrong with you?

126
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,060
I'm helping you. This is what I get?

127
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,500
Your ideas are so lousy.

128
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,280
Alright.

129
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,160
Weilan.

130
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:04,680
Weilan!

131
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,840
Put some effort in!

132
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,940
Coach Lu, have you seen Weilan?

133
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,300
Can't you look for yourself?

134
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,060
Where could she go?

135
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:22,840
Fine, I'm leaving.

136
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,180
- Where to?
- To find her.

137
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,380
The spike is in vain.

138
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,640
Dad.

139
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:14,800
Dad.

140
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,900
I've packed most of the things.

141
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:18,700
I've booked tomorrow's flight.

142
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,380
You're too strict with Weilan.

143
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,580
I still think

144
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,960
whether she plays beach volleyball

145
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,780
or does other sports,

146
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,110
as long as

147
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:33,130
she likes it,

148
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,460
we as adults should support her.

149
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,080
Dad,

150
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,380
I'm not against her playing.

151
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,980
She'll have better opportunities abroad.

152
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,160
Rest assured.

153
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,360
I've arranged

154
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,860
a good school for her over there.

155
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,740
How could I be at ease?

156
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,610
What's so great about abroad?

157
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,360
Is their education

158
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,100
really better than ours?

159
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,840
If so, why do they still lose

160
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,380
to us in some competitions?

161
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,040
Yes, yes.

162
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,580
That's not what I meant, Dad.

163
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:02,860
You've misunderstood me.

164
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,320
Look.

165
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,960
We have

166
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,220
the financial means now.

167
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:08,960
While Weilan is young,

168
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,400
sending her abroad to gain

169
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,480
more experience and learn

170
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,660
isn't a bad thing.

171
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,000
I've checked out

172
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,140
their beach volleyball team.

173
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:18,180
They don't even have a professional coach.

174
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:21,040
They're just relying on the kids'

175
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,740
physical fitness and skills.

176
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,000
In the long run,

177
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,420
it's a waste of time.

178
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,740
And Dad, you see

179
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,740
Weilan's wrist

180
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,460
needs to be treated.

181
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,900
If she continues like this,

182
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,980
she might not be able to play anymore.

183
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,180
I'm doing this for her good.

184
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,740
I hope you can support me.

185
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,540
Anyway, on this matter,

186
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,100
Weilan and I are of one mind.

187
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,900
As long as she agrees,

188
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,140
I won't oppose it.

189
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:55,100
You're her mom. You talk to her.

190
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,640
Duoduo, come on.

191
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:06,660
Come in.

192
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,320
Thanks, Grandpa.

193
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,780
Here to see Weilan?

194
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,060
Is she here?

195
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,560
Hi, Auntie.

196
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:14,880
Hello.

197
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:16,780
Are you leaving, Auntie?

198
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,360
Yes.

199
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,320
Sit for a while.

200
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,380
I'll continue packing.

201
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,020
She's leaving.

202
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,460
So is Weilan.

203
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:26,980
They're going abroad.

204
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,020
Weilan's going abroad?

205
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:31,220
Why suddenly?

206
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,120
Her mom thinks

207
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,460
it's better for her development,

208
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,720
and her hand

209
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,900
hasn't healed.

210
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,740
She's taking her for treatment.

211
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,380
It's all for her good.

212
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,160
Yes.

213
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,820
It's all for the kid's good.

214
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,830
- Hello?
- Weilan.

215
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,700
I've packed your luggage.

216
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,580
I've booked tomorrow's flight.

217
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,820
I hope you

218
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,820
think carefully.

219
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,180
If you agree,

220
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,220
come with me tomorrow.

221
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,520
Alright.

222
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:33,900
I'll go abroad with you.

223
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:35,960
Good.

224
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,180
I'll wait for you at home.

225
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,280
I'm sorry.

226
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,340
I came to apologize.

227
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,560
I shouldn't have said

228
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:19,820
those hurtful things.

229
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,460
I'm not mad.

230
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,080
That's good.

231
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:29,880
By the way,

232
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,520
why didn't you train today?

233
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,580
You didn't answer my calls.

234
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,240
You don't know

235
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,700
how worried they were, like ants on a hot pan.

236
00:12:37,420 --> 00:12:38,460
Only I could find you.

237
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,440
Did something happen?

238
00:12:42,710 --> 00:12:43,980
Nothing.

239
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,100
It's just that maybe...

240
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:51,720
Weilan,

241
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,780
I don't know what happened,

242
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,180
but I'll support

243
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,900
any decision you make.

244
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:11,120
Thanks.

245
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:26,880
Bon voyage.

246
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,220
For our dreams.

247
00:13:58,960 --> 00:13:59,800
Duoduo.

248
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:01,000
What's wrong?

249
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:01,840
You look so worried.

250
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:06,060
I just went to find Chen Weilan.

251
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:07,980
Grandpa said

252
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,980
she might go abroad.

253
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:11,920
Going abroad?

254
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:13,900
She didn't mention it.

255
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:19,020
Because her hand hasn't healed,

256
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,880
and her mom thinks

257
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,300
it's better for her development.

258
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,580
You don't want her to go?

259
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:28,460
Of course.

260
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,820
Our team just won the new league championship.

261
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,240
We were finally becoming

262
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,500
more in sync.

263
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,300
But if she's really going,

264
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:39,100
I have to support her.

265
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:42,480
But Duoduo,

266
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,140
have you asked her yourself?

267
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:46,600
Right.

268
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:47,820
I only heard about it.

269
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,960
I haven't asked her directly.

270
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:50,800
Right?

271
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,340
I'll go ask her.

272
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,580
Are you really leaving?

273
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,820
Do you have to go abroad?

274
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:31,900
If I don't

275
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,140
heal my hand,

276
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,520
I won't be able

277
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,020
to play,

278
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,460
let alone with you.

279
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:43,900
So I agreed to go with my mom.

280
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,060
When are you leaving?

281
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:55,800
Tomorrow.

282
00:15:58,280 --> 00:15:59,120
For how long?

283
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,320
Will you come back?

284
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,820
I don't know how long I'll be gone.

285
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:18,460
I never thought you'd really leave.

286
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:23,980
But since you've decided,

287
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:27,320
I'll support you.

288
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:37,520
Duoduo,

289
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,940
thank you for helping me

290
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,180
with my mental block.

291
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:49,100
But no one can

292
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,100
help me with my hand.

293
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,460
I have to face it myself.

294
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,120
So while I'm away,

295
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:04,300
